<DESCRIPT>  FRUIT; RECIPE  </DESCRIPT>
<LEADPARA>  Legend doesn't say what George Washington planned to do with all the fruit on
the tree he chopped down, but perhaps he planned to soak it in sugar syrup and
liqueur to make maraschino cherries. If so, he surely shouldn't have been
punished for that.; Here are some way to use maraschino cherries from the
National Cherry Foundation:  </LEADPARA>
<SECTION>  Food  </SECTION>
<HEADLINE>  IT'S A JUBILEE
MARASCHINO CHERRIES ADD
A BIT OF BRIGHT COLOR AND
LOTS OF SWEET FRUIT TASTE
TO YOUR FAVORITE DESSERTS  </HEADLINE>
<MEMO>  Recipes of the Week  </MEMO>
<TEXT>  (check) Add maraschino cherries and nuts to your favorite brownie recipe.;
(check) Add cherries to your favorite chocolate-chip cookie recipe.; (check)
For a light iced treat, combine chopped cherries with vanilla yogurt and
thawed frozen whipped topping; freeze and serve.; (check) Add a bit of
maraschino cherry juice to hot chocolate and top with whipped cream, shaved
chocolate and a cherry.;  MARASCHINO ANGEL CAKE; 1 cup cake flour;  1/2 cup
powdered sugar;  1/2 cup finely chopped maraschino cherries, well-drained; 1
1/2 cups (10 to 12) eggs whites; 1 1/2 teaspoons cream of tartar; 1 cup
granulated sugar;  1/4 teaspoon salt;  1/2 teaspoon almond extract;  Cherry
Icing;  Whole cherries with stems;   Heat oven to 350 degrees. Mix flour and
powdered sugar. Place chopped cherries on several layers of paper towels to
remove all liquid. Beat egg whites and cream of tartar in large mixer bowl on
medium until foamy. Beat in granulated sugar, about 2 tablespoons at a time.
Add salt and almond extract; continue beating mixture until stiff and glossy.
Lightly fold in flour-sugar mixture, 3 to 4 tablespoons at a time; fold only
until dry ingredients are no longer visible. Fold cherries into batter. Spoon
batter into ungreased 10-inch fluted or regular tube pan. Cut through batter
with a spatula to remove air pockets. Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until top
springs back when lightly touched. Invert pan on a heat-proof funnel or bottle
until completely cooled. Remove from pan. Ice and decorate with maraschino
cherries.;    Cherry Icing: Mix 1 cup powdered sugar, 1 tablespoon softened
butter or margarine, 1 1/2 teaspoons maraschino liquid, 1/4 teaspoon almond
extract and about 2 tablespoons milk until mixture comes to desired
consistency. Makes 1/2 cup.;  MARASCHINO CHERRY LOAF;  1/2 cup milk; 2
tablespoons sugar;  1/2 teaspoon salt;  1/2 cup butter, softened;  1/4 cup
warm water (105 to 115 degrees); 1 package active dry yeast; 1 egg; 2 1/4 to 2
3/4 cups flour, divided;  1/2 cup red cherries, drained;  1/4 cup each
seedless raisins and coarsely chopped walnuts;  1/2 teaspoon grated lemon
peel;  1/4 teaspoon ground cinnamon;  Scald milk; stir in sugar, salt and
butter. Cool to lukewarm. Measure warm water into large warm bowl. Sprinkle in
yeast; stir until dissolved. Add lukewarm milk mixture, egg and 1 cup flour;
beat about 1 minute or until smooth. Stir in about 1 1/4 cups additional flour
to make a stiff batter. Cover with dish towel. Refrigerate 2 hours. Meanwhile,
coarsely chop drained cherries and drain thoroughly on paper towels. Combine
cherries, raisins, lemon peel and cinnamon; set aside. Stir dough down. On a
floured board, knead in cherry mixture. Roll dough to a 12-by-8 1/2-inch
rectangle. Starting with short edge, roll up dough, jelly-roll fashion; pinch
seam and ends to seal. Fold under ends. Place, seam-side down, in a greased 8
1/2-by-4 1/2-by-2 1/2-inch loaf pan. Cover; let rise in warm place about 1
hour or until doubled. Bake at 350 degrees. 45 to 50 minutes or until loaf
sounds hollow when tapped with finger. Remove from pan; cool on wire rack.; 
FRUITED MARASCHINO CHERRY CREPES;  1/2 cup red cherries, drained and divided;
1 pound ricotta cheese; 1 teaspoon sugar;  1/8 teaspoon grated orange peel; 
Dash salt; 1 can (11 oz.) mandarin orange segments, drained; 8 crepes (recipe
below);  1/2 cup peach preserves;   Coarsely chop cherries; reserve 1/4 cup.
Combine remaining cherries with cheese, sugar, orange peel, salt and orange
segments. Place 1/3 cup mixture along one side of each crepe; roll up. Place
in single layer in buttered shallow baking dish. Combine reserved cherries
with peach preserves. Spoon over crepes. Bake at 400 degrees. 10 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.;    Crepes: Combine 2 eggs, 3/4 cup milk, 1/2 cup flour, 2
teaspoons each sugar and melted butter or margarine and dash salt; beat until
blended. Heat a lightly greased 6- or 7-inch skillet over medium-high heat.
Add 2 tablespoons batter; tilt skillet to spread batter. Cook about 30 seconds
or until lightly browned; turn and cook on second side. Repeat with remaining
batter. Makes about 8 crepes.;  MARASCHINO CHERRY FRUIT CUP (Microwave
Method); 1 medium grapefruit, peeled and sectioned (about 2 cups); 1 medium
orange, peeled and sectioned (about 1 cup); 1 medium apple, pared and diced
(about 1 cup);  1/2 cup red maraschino cherries, drained;  1/4 cup orange
juice; 2 tablespoons cherry syrup; 1 tablespoon lemon juice; 1 cinnamon stick;
6 whole cloves;  Fresh mint for garnish (optional);  Combine grapefruit,
orange, apple and cherries; set aside. In a microwave dish, combine orange
juice, cherry syrup, lemon juice, cinnamon stick and cloves. Microwave at high
30 to 45 seconds or until mixture comes to boil. Pour over fruit mixture.
Refrigerate, covered, several hours; stir occasionally. Serve in individual
dessert dishes. Garnish each serving with fresh mint. Makes 8 servings.;   
Note: Recipe developed for 600- to 700-watt microwave ovens.;  CHERRY PEANUT
BUTTER; MUFFINS; 2 cups flour;  1/3 cup sugar; 2 1/2 teaspoons baking powder; 
1/2 teaspoon salt and grated orange peel;  1/2 cup peanut butter; 2
tablespoons butter or margarine;  1/2 cup red maraschino cherries, chopped; 
2/3 cup milk; 2 eggs, slightly beaten;   In medium bowl, mix flour, sugar,
baking powder, salt and orange peel; cut in peanut and butter until mixture
resembles coarse crumbs. Stir in cherries. Combine milk and eggs; add to dry
ingredients and stir just until mixed. Spoon batter into 12 greased 3-inch
muffin cups. Bake at 400 degrees about 15 minutes or until wooden pick
inserted near center comes out clean. Makes 12 muffins.;  CHERRY OATMEAL
COOKIES; 1 1/4 cups flour;  1/2 teaspoon ground cinnamon;  1/4 teaspoon each
salt and baking soda;  1/2 cup butter or margarine, softened; 1 cup packed
dark brown sugar; 1 egg;  1/2 teaspoon vanilla;  1/4 cup milk; 1 teaspoon
vinegar; 1 cup quick-cooking rolled oats;  1/2 cup red maraschino cherries,
chopped;  Red maraschino cherry halves, if desired;  Mix flour, cinnamon, salt
and baking soda. Cream butter and sugar. Add egg and vanilla; beat until
fluffy. Combine milk and vinegar, add to sugar mixture. Add flour mixture; mix
until blended. Add oats; mix well. Gently fold in chopped cherries. Drop by
teaspoons onto cookie sheets, leaving 2 inches between cookies. Press a cherry
half into center of cookie, if desired. Bake at 375 degrees 10 to 12 minutes
or until lightly browned around edges. Cool on wire racks. Makes about 3 dozen.  </TEXT>
